Collecting and presenting data about the state and performance of applications
There are three different types of monitoring
    Infrastructure monitoring - focuses on infrastructure eg CPU
    Application Performance Monitoring - focuses on performance and stability of individual parts of an application eg response time, logs
    
 // Infrastructure Monitoring
 Examples:
   Sensu
   NewRelic
   
   
// Application Performance Monitoring
Examples:
    AppDynamics
    NewRelic
    
    
// Aggregation and Analytics - collecting monitoring data and doing something with it
                             - Most monitoring tools have aggregation and analytics features
Examples:
     Elastic Stack
